  {
    "id": "UgywVFzl4VpRarTTCad4AaABAg",
    "author": "@Pystro",
    "author_channel_id": "UCWKuGcrDx6bylfub0FjMLVw",
    "text": "All the bands really do is keep the outer rollers from contacting each other. They don't directly contribute to the bearing functionality. The rollers do all of that.",
    "likes": 2,
    "published_at": "2025-03-19T16:44:01Z",
    "reply_count": 2,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgywVFzl4VpRarTTCad4AaABAg.AFrLPArtWbPAFrS3rKw4E-",
        "author": "@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "author_channel_id": "UC4AkVj-qnJxNtKuz3rkq16A",
        "text": "that doesn't seem right - if that were true why have the bands at all? I think the bands ensure it is all rolling friction",
        "likes": 0,
        "published_at": "2025-03-19T17:42:17Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "UgywVFzl4VpRarTTCad4AaABAg.AFrLPArtWbPAFrUNAuktsi",
        "author": "@Pystro",
        "author_channel_id": "UCWKuGcrDx6bylfub0FjMLVw",
        "text": "@ThinkingandTinkering Yes, the bands do in fact ensure it's all rolling friction. If the outer rollers touch each other, then that causes sliding friction.",
        "likes": 0,
        "published_at": "2025-03-19T18:02:23Z"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "UgyhdBP7yJQJgZrAxyt4AaABAg",
    "author": "@Pystro",
    "author_channel_id": "UCWKuGcrDx6bylfub0FjMLVw",
    "text": "Your arrangement was unstable because you wound your bands wrong. The order is supposed to be ABCDDCBA. And yes, the D direction will be least stabilized, but with the right arrangement the rollers will at least generally want to be parallel.\nHowever, with 4 outside rollers you can halve the number of bands if you wind them only around 2 of the rollers. The bottom layer is two bands going west-east, the next two layers are going north-south, and the final layer is going west-east again. In fact, any even number of outside rollers can be made to work as a 4-high stack.",
    "likes": 5,
    "published_at": "2025-03-19T16:28:46Z",
    "reply_count": 1,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgyhdBP7yJQJgZrAxyt4AaABAg.AFrJeTL0524AFrRr0FpW6h",
        "author": "@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "author_channel_id": "UC4AkVj-qnJxNtKuz3rkq16A",
        "text": "cheers mate - i re-arranged it as you suggested",
        "likes": 2,
        "published_at": "2025-03-19T17:40:23Z"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "UgwViNJ13qRqsBWKGcd4AaABAg",
    "author": "@JorgTheElder",
    "author_channel_id": "UC7PiyC1YNing3Blska_yAoA",
    "text": "Seems like it would be better to flip the C-shape of the band 180 from band to band instead of just 90. Then a 4 outer roller version should be fairly stable with just 3 bands.",
    "likes": 0,
    "published_at": "2025-03-19T16:15:47Z",
    "reply_count": 1,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgwViNJ13qRqsBWKGcd4AaABAg.AFrIAKFth-vAFrRkIzWn9-",
        "author": "@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "author_channel_id": "UC4AkVj-qnJxNtKuz3rkq16A",
        "text": "the patent says 90 - I also tried 180 and it didn't seem to make any difference - so i left it as the patent said",
        "likes": 0,
        "published_at": "2025-03-19T17:39:28Z"
      }
    ]
  },
